1
00:00:00,350 --> 00:00:04,410
Characters, actions, places, occupations,

2
00:00:04,520 --> 00:00:09,400
and events in this series are fictional
and created for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:14,100
They are not intended to urge
or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:16,520
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:22,100
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

6
00:00:24,540 --> 00:00:26,460
I wish you get to do what you love.

7
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,660
I wish you can start your own company.

8
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:33,260
I wish you’ll be a lovely girlfriend to me
for a long time.

9
00:00:34,290 --> 00:00:38,860
I wish we can celebrate your birthday
together every year.

10
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,060
4 YEARS AGO.

11
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:43,500
-Blow the candles. It’s hot.
-Wait a sec.

12
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:46,300
Come on. Blow them.

13
00:00:46,340 --> 00:00:47,380
Will you promise me…

14
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:50,780
that we will spend my birthday together
every year?

15
00:00:52,460 --> 00:00:53,260
Sure.

16
00:00:53,980 --> 00:00:56,460
I will never let anyone
hold your birthday cake.

17
00:01:06,740 --> 00:01:09,900
-Yay! Happy Birthday, Prim!
-Happy birthday.

18
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:24,820
1 YEAR AGO.

19
00:01:44,660 --> 00:01:46,300
Happy f*cking birthday.

20
00:02:47,690 --> 00:02:48,400
Cut.

21
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:59,500
Joy, can you move around
and go with the flow more?

22
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:00,300
Sure.

23
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:02,060
Shasha is so beautiful.

24
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:03,850
She looks good at every angle.

25
00:03:04,140 --> 00:03:05,140
Her face is so unique.

26
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:05,860
Really?

27
00:03:05,940 --> 00:03:08,260
But I see you say the same compliment
to every model, Joy.

28
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:10,850
Please do what I said.

29
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:11,820
Yes.

30
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:16,460
Prim, can I unbutton her jacket?

31
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:17,650
I think it will look cooler.

32
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,060
Of course.

33
00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:20,760
I trust your fashion sense.

34
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:24,050
Even if you compliment me,
I won’t give you a discount on my fee.

35
00:03:30,890 --> 00:03:32,000
Can you unbutton the jacket?

36
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:35,700
You do it.

37
00:03:37,430 --> 00:03:39,090
When you unbutton it,
I’ll arrange your jacket.

38
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:41,350
I’m a model, not a stylist.

39
00:03:42,170 --> 00:03:43,090
Don’t you know what your job is?

40
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:45,000
Yes, I do.

41
00:03:45,170 --> 00:03:46,950
But I thought
you would help make it easier.

42
00:04:08,510 --> 00:04:10,450
Let’s do it again.

43
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:12,100
Please maintain
the cool look like earlier.

44
00:04:12,130 --> 00:04:14,100
You can go with the flow of the music.

45
00:04:18,910 --> 00:04:20,600
We can’t work overtime today.

46
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,000
I won’t.

47
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,900
But look at the model your client chose.

48
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,290
Is she going to keep shooting
until our memory card is full?

49
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:28,400
Why are you nagging her?

50
00:04:28,530 --> 00:04:29,800
Why do you dislike her so much?

51
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:30,930
Did she steal your girlfriend?

52
00:04:32,930 --> 00:04:33,850
I don’t dislike her.

53
00:04:34,110 --> 00:04:35,150
But I just find her smug.

54
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:37,170
Her fee is so damn high.

55
00:04:37,650 --> 00:04:40,400
It takes up most of the budget
for the production.

56
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,680
Who are you? Why did you take my picture?

57
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:03,850
I’m a trainee.

58
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:05,600
I’m your long-time fan.

59
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:07,740
I took the picture as a memory.

60
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:10,200
Are you here as a trainee or as a fan?

61
00:05:11,930 --> 00:05:13,850
Shasha, I’ll take care of it.

62
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:16,240
I already told the staff
not to take your picture.

63
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,400
She’s new.

64
00:05:17,770 --> 00:05:19,400
I’ll warn her. I’m sorry.

65
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:22,610
You should be more professional.

66
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:24,200
How can you let this happen?

67
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,150
Woon, I’m not in the mood for shooting.

68
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,680
I need time to calm down.

69
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:31,700
Let her have a break.

70
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:38,300
If she takes a break,
we may need to work overtime.

71
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:40,400
We only need a few more shots
to wrap up the shooting.

72
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:53,200
Andy.

73
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:54,200
Yes?

74
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:55,770
Did you check everything?

75
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:57,070
Nothing can go wrong.

76
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:58,300
Of course, Mrs. Nin.

77
00:05:58,470 --> 00:06:00,570
I took care of everything.

78
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,750
Where is Dada?

79
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:02,980
She has arrived.

80
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:04,200
She’s getting her makeup done.

81
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,610
Hurry up and get it done
before the finale walk.

82
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:06,560
Sure.

83
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:08,730
Come on. We don’t have much time.

84
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:09,570
Hurry up.

85
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:31,100
Hi.

86
00:06:31,970 --> 00:06:32,800
Bambi!

87
00:06:32,970 --> 00:06:34,159
When did you get back?

88
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:35,500
I flew back this morning.

89
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,070
I came back in time to attend this show
at my mom’s request.

90
00:06:38,490 --> 00:06:39,580
You’ve been away for so long.

91
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:45,000
Is that the finale dress?

92
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,780
It’s beautiful.

93
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,500
Yes, it’s really beautiful.

94
00:06:48,770 --> 00:06:51,250
Your mom’s designs are always trendy.

95
00:06:52,060 --> 00:06:54,850
A beautiful dress
is for a beautiful woman.

96
00:08:40,179 --> 00:08:41,299
Thank you for today.

97
00:08:41,409 --> 00:08:43,400
I gave you a little extra
for the overtime.

98
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,690
It’s okay, Gorya.

99
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:46,600
Instead, you can buy me drinks later.

100
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:49,010
Are you going to Prim’s birthday party
at Blossom?

101
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,850
I won’t miss it.

102
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:52,000
See you there.

103
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:54,070
Okay. Is there anything else
I can help with?

104
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,410
I need to go home and doll up.

105
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,570
You should go.
You seem to need a lot of dolling up.

106
00:08:57,730 --> 00:08:59,640
You are so mean.

107
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,170
-I’m leaving.
-You should go. See you later.

108
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:02,050
Bye.

109
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,680
Can you unzip the dress?

110
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,400
Where is your manager?

111
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,700
She went to the car to get something.

112
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,850
Are you going to Blossom tonight?

113
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:21,500
Yes.

114
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:23,170
It’s Prim’s birthday.

115
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,850
I’ve asked you to go to the club with me.

116
00:09:27,950 --> 00:09:29,150
But you said no every time.

117
00:09:31,590 --> 00:09:32,500
I don’t like you

118
00:09:32,830 --> 00:09:33,700
You’re not my type.

119
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:38,370
What is your type?

120
00:09:38,730 --> 00:09:39,800
I can be your type.

121
00:09:41,930 --> 00:09:42,800
So cocky.

122
00:09:43,410 --> 00:09:45,450
Not everyone likes you.

123
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,980
Won’t you give me any chance?

124
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,200
You're not my type.

125
00:09:50,380 --> 00:09:52,130
No matter how much you try,
my answer is still no.

126
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:54,950
Aren’t you too quick to judge?

127
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:09,450
Sha.

128
00:10:11,590 --> 00:10:12,530
Are you done?

129
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:14,250
Why does it take you so long
to change your outfit?

130
00:10:16,330 --> 00:10:17,980
I asked Gorya to unzip for me.

131
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:27,570
Do you really need to get her?

132
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:30,700
She’s challenging.

133
00:10:33,170 --> 00:10:34,000
Hurry up.

134
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,340
Why didn’t you tell me
that you came back?

135
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,300
I wanted to surprise you.

136
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:44,370
I thought you liked theatrics.

137
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,350
Stop getting on my nerves.

138
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,610
You ruined my show.

139
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,900
You lied to Dada
that I wanted you to do the finale walk.

140
00:10:49,010 --> 00:10:50,650
I’ve worked for this show for months.

141
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:51,580
It’s all ruined.

142
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:52,450
Ruined? How?

143
00:10:52,690 --> 00:10:53,960
Everyone is talking about it.

144
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,380
They all l want to know where I’ve been.

145
00:10:56,650 --> 00:10:57,890
I planned to announce it
on the microphone.

146
00:10:58,030 --> 00:10:59,100
But you stopped me.

147
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,700
How long are you going to stay?

148
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,000
What do you plan to do?

149
00:11:08,990 --> 00:11:10,700
I sent you to school, but you dropped out.

150
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,200
Why do I need to study?

151
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,900
When I can leech off you.

152
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,000
Am I right?

153
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:18,600
Stop being sarcastic.

154
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,500
If you’re going to come back
and live with me,

155
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:22,100
you’d better behave.

156
00:11:22,690 --> 00:11:24,300
Otherwise, I will send you back.

157
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:27,000
This time, you will have no choice.

158
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:10,390
Cheers.

159
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:13,780
Excuse me. I’ll be right back.

160
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:17,540
Happy birthday, Prim.

161
00:12:18,990 --> 00:12:20,220
You turned 25.

162
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:21,620
You are at the crucial age of 25.

163
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:25,660
It’s the year where you will either
rise to the top or fall to rock bottom.

164
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:28,060
Ant, you are cursing me, aren’t you?

165
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:30,780
I will never fall.

166
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:34,060
Because I got everything under control.

167
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,460
Yes, you do.

168
00:12:36,780 --> 00:12:38,860
When you turn 40,

169
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:42,400
you will realize
nothing is under your control.

170
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:45,660
Ant, you don’t look like
you’re in your 40s.

171
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:47,010
You look like you're about our age.

172
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:49,580
Min.

173
00:12:50,020 --> 00:12:51,860
You really mean it when you said that.

174
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:53,460
Well said, sister.

175
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:57,960
Hey, her boyfriend would be upset
if he saw you kiss her.

176
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:00,600
He doesn’t like it
when she hangs out with us.

177
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:03,200
We are just like sisters.

178
00:13:03,830 --> 00:13:05,200
I have a girlfriend.

179
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:08,920
More importantly,
I’m done with straight girls.

180
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:12,140
I don’t want to fall for
straight girls again.

181
00:13:15,150 --> 00:13:17,980
Prim, do you have anything you want
for your birthday this year?

182
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:21,860
No.

183
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:23,820
I’m happy with my work.

184
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:24,980
I make enough money.

185
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:26,340
I help my mom and sister
to live comfortably.

186
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:27,900
I have good friends.

187
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:28,940
That is enough for me.

188
00:13:30,460 --> 00:13:33,420
If you’re always busy with work,
when will you find a girlfriend?

189
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:38,340
I haven’t found anyone
good enough to date.

190
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:40,340
So I’m just enjoying my life for now.

191
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:42,740
Right?

192
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,540
You said I was boasting about my life.

193
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,540
Let’s drink it up, Ant.

194
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:47,980
You, too.

195
00:13:48,980 --> 00:13:50,340
Can I have fun with you?

196
00:13:55,580 --> 00:13:56,860
Cheers.

197
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:59,580
Cheers. Bottoms up.

198
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:01,420
Praew.

199
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:07,600
Can you take a picture for us?

200
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:10,020
Let’s take a picture.

201
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:19,940
Alright. One, two, three.

202
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:24,340
Okay.

203
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:26,820
Beautiful.

204
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:38,010
PARK: I’M WAITING AT THE ENTRANCE.

205
00:14:44,710 --> 00:14:47,540
When will you finish it?
I see you’ve been drinking it for a while.

206
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:00,420
Why are you here?

207
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:02,290
I’m not going back with you.
Today is Prim’s birthday.

208
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:03,740
Why didn’t you answer my call?

209
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:04,620
What were you doing?

210
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:06,140
I was having fun with my friends.

211
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:08,000
I wasn’t staring at the phone
all the time.

212
00:15:08,780 --> 00:15:10,140
You meet them every day.

213
00:15:10,330 --> 00:15:11,490
Isn’t that enough?

214
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:12,980
Why?

215
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:15,420
Are you going back to her place
to celebrate her birthday?

216
00:15:16,380 --> 00:15:17,470
Are you crazy?

217
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:18,860
You get jealous because of Prim.

218
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,850
Why? I can’t do that?

219
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:22,340
This is too much, Park.

220
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,890
If you’re going act like a jerk,
maybe we should break up.

221
00:15:28,590 --> 00:15:31,050
Are you breaking up with me
to date a girl?

222
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:34,020
If you like women,
why didn’t you date them?

223
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,100
Why the f*ck are you dating me?

224
00:15:35,590 --> 00:15:36,930
No need for the F word.

225
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:39,100
I can date anyone I want.

226
00:15:39,330 --> 00:15:41,370
I’m breaking up with you
because you are a jerk.

227
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:43,600
I let you mistreat me for too long.

228
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:47,820
Hey.

229
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:50,550
Let me go.

230
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:53,200
You need to go home to talk.

231
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:54,300
I’m not going.

232
00:15:54,410 --> 00:15:55,450
I’m going back in.

233
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:56,460
You must come home with me.

234
00:15:56,610 --> 00:15:58,200
I’m not going.

235
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:01,900
Did you push me?

236
00:16:02,010 --> 00:16:03,700
I should have done it a long time ago.

237
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:10,500
Don’t attack her from the back.

238
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,100
She broke up with you.

239
00:16:12,220 --> 00:16:13,140
You should have walked away.

240
00:16:13,420 --> 00:16:14,800
It’s none of your damn business, lesbo!

241
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:16,620
I’m a lesbian. So what?

242
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:18,950
It’s none of your f*cking business.

243
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:23,100
-Stop it.
-Help. Help me.

244
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:25,100
This man is going to hit me.

245
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:26,740
Please call the police.

246
00:16:27,110 --> 00:16:29,850
Take a video of his behavior.

247
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:35,310
-Let’s call the police.
-How could he hit a woman?

248
00:16:36,770 --> 00:16:38,550
He was going to hit her.

249
00:16:39,710 --> 00:16:41,370
Min, let’s go. I’ll give you a ride home.

250
00:16:43,930 --> 00:16:44,490
Let’s go.

251
00:16:44,610 --> 00:16:45,610
I can go home by myself.

252
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:55,370
What the heck are you filming?

253
00:17:06,010 --> 00:17:07,099
Thank you.

254
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:09,349
He is threatening when he is mad.

255
00:17:11,950 --> 00:17:13,099
Are you okay?

256
00:17:14,650 --> 00:17:16,599
Don’t worry. I can handle it.

257
00:17:20,060 --> 00:17:22,150
It’s good that you broke up with him.

258
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:24,150
He didn’t show you any respect.

259
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:26,750
Yes.

260
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:29,800
I should have broken up with him
a long time ago.

261
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:33,800
But you need to be careful.

262
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:36,620
A guy like him may not let go easily.

263
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:48,600
Did he grab you this hard?

264
00:17:50,020 --> 00:17:51,100
Your wrist is all red.

265
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:52,700
There are also fingernail scratches.

266
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:55,000
Shall we go inside and treat your wound?

267
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:56,540
You must be really hurt.

268
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:03,020
It’s okay.

269
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:04,460
Thanks a lot.

270
