546
00:37:46,450 --> 00:37:48,560
They portray what women
have been through in life.

547
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:52,900
This woman was in a toxic relationship.

548
00:37:54,530 --> 00:37:55,600
She stayed in the relationship

549
00:37:57,420 --> 00:37:58,540
because she was scared.

550
00:38:01,140 --> 00:38:02,100
What was she scared of?

551
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:06,200
She was scared that no one would love her.

552
00:38:14,870 --> 00:38:16,450
Do you want me to take your picture?

553
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:19,340
No.

554
00:38:19,790 --> 00:38:20,600
I’m very shy.

555
00:38:21,050 --> 00:38:24,950
My life is not that interesting.

556
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,820
Every life is interesting.

557
00:38:29,590 --> 00:38:30,870
It’s up to who is looking at it.

558
00:38:32,620 --> 00:38:33,570
I have to decline it.

559
00:38:34,060 --> 00:38:35,800
But I want to ask you to work with me.

560
00:38:36,050 --> 00:38:38,310
My client wants a photoshoot
with a girl power concept like this.

561
00:38:40,250 --> 00:38:43,000
Sure. I’m happy to work with you.

562
00:39:22,110 --> 00:39:23,770
I think you need to come up
with a new concept.

563
00:39:23,830 --> 00:39:25,050
It has to be sharper than this.

564
00:39:25,540 --> 00:39:28,000
Go back and fix it. I’ll help you review.

565
00:39:28,180 --> 00:39:28,850
Yes.

566
00:39:43,820 --> 00:39:45,200
I’m here to apply for a job, Prim.

567
00:39:47,220 --> 00:39:48,460
What are you doing, Bambi?

568
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:49,850
What do you want?

569
00:39:52,970 --> 00:39:54,170
I’m not kidding.

570
00:39:54,420 --> 00:39:55,800
I’m here to apply for a job.

571
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:58,360
I don’t want to live aimlessly anymore.

572
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,850
I want to be useful.

573
00:40:01,980 --> 00:40:03,250
Then what are you doing?

574
00:40:03,820 --> 00:40:05,300
There’s no job for you here.

575
00:40:08,620 --> 00:40:10,550
Can’t you find a job for your friend?

576
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:19,080
I want to be a better person.

577
00:40:20,650 --> 00:40:22,000
I’m trying.

578
00:40:23,490 --> 00:40:24,800
I need your support.

579
00:40:36,130 --> 00:40:37,000
Or…

580
00:40:37,950 --> 00:40:39,570
why don’t you hire me as your secretary?

581
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:46,600
You know…

582
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,470
how good I am at taking care of you.

583
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:11,300
Go find a job somewhere else.

584
00:41:11,930 --> 00:41:13,000
There’s no job for you here.

585
00:41:13,850 --> 00:41:17,400
We don’t accept unpredictable people
to work here.

586
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:19,730
Those who one moment want to be together,

587
00:41:22,050 --> 00:41:23,400
the next moment want to break up.

588
00:41:57,310 --> 00:42:00,200
(Will you promise me that we will spend
my birthday together every year?)

589
00:42:00,930 --> 00:42:01,700
(Sure.)

590
00:42:01,860 --> 00:42:04,400
(I’ll never let anyone
hold your birthday cake.)

591
00:42:05,670 --> 00:42:06,450
Can I eat it now?

592
00:42:06,540 --> 00:42:07,300
Yes.

593
00:42:07,580 --> 00:42:08,740
Come. I’ll eat it now.

594
00:42:09,350 --> 00:42:11,200
(I wish you get to do what you love.)

595
00:42:12,790 --> 00:42:14,710
(I wish you can start your own company.)

596
00:42:16,330 --> 00:42:19,330
(I wish you’ll be a lovely girlfriend
to me for a long time.)

597
00:42:27,450 --> 00:42:31,180
Is it that hard to say you love me first?

598
00:42:31,500 --> 00:42:32,820
If I do that,

599
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:35,980
will you be my girlfriend?

600
00:42:38,060 --> 00:42:40,940
From now on, you can take care of me
as your girlfriend.

601
00:42:42,260 --> 00:42:43,100
Here.

602
00:43:51,970 --> 00:43:54,100
I’m creating a new brand.
Its target is teenagers.

603
00:43:54,820 --> 00:43:56,500
Why don’t you learn about the business?

604
00:43:57,730 --> 00:44:00,800
It’s better than partying every night
and causing trouble.

605
00:44:02,710 --> 00:44:04,390
You’re only worried that
I will cause trouble.

606
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:07,170
Have you ever asked
how I was doing when I lived abroad?

607
00:44:08,810 --> 00:44:10,350
All you want to do is send me away.

608
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:17,500
Hello, Yanin.

609
00:44:21,220 --> 00:44:23,400
Shasha, my model.

610
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:26,300
You are the prettiest.

611
00:44:27,210 --> 00:44:28,700
I look pretty because of your dress.

612
00:44:28,740 --> 00:44:30,500
Your designs are always trendy.

613
00:44:30,540 --> 00:44:31,770
People of all ages love it.

614
00:44:34,660 --> 00:44:37,700
Shasha, this is Bambi, my daughter.

615
00:44:38,120 --> 00:44:39,580
She just came back from the U.S.

616
00:44:40,410 --> 00:44:41,900
I think you two are the same age.

617
00:44:43,500 --> 00:44:44,850
Nice to meet you.

618
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:50,200
Nice to meet you.

619
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:53,540
Excuse me. I’ll let you two talk.

620
00:44:58,080 --> 00:45:00,500
I often saw you on fashion accounts on IG.

621
00:45:01,310 --> 00:45:02,250
I’m your fan.

622
00:45:03,390 --> 00:45:04,250
Thank you.

623
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:06,650
I’ve heard your name a lot.

624
00:45:07,170 --> 00:45:08,390
I finally met you.

625
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:10,470
Really?

626
00:45:10,520 --> 00:45:11,740
People talked about me?

627
00:45:11,840 --> 00:45:13,600
What did they say? Tell me.

628
00:45:14,430 --> 00:45:15,580
Did they say nice things about me?

629
00:45:16,220 --> 00:45:17,400
Of course.

630
00:45:17,910 --> 00:45:21,210
Someone like you
has nothing bad to be said about.

631
00:45:23,130 --> 00:45:24,140
I hope it is true.

632
00:45:37,380 --> 00:45:39,800
It’s good that my mom
changed her design style.

633
00:45:42,900 --> 00:45:46,200
I think her previous collections
are a bit outdated.

634
00:45:49,810 --> 00:45:51,800
Do you like it because I’m wearing it?

635
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:56,700
When you have a good model,
any outfit can look good.

636
00:46:00,010 --> 00:46:02,500
I like you. You have high self-confidence.

637
00:46:05,500 --> 00:46:06,740
I think we can be friends.

638
00:46:08,930 --> 00:46:11,420
Sure. Let’s get to know each other.

639
00:46:18,480 --> 00:46:20,100
Do you want to do something fun with me?

640
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:27,500
1 WEEK LATER.

641
00:46:27,540 --> 00:46:28,420
Prim.

642
00:46:29,290 --> 00:46:30,400
Gorya.

643
00:46:30,970 --> 00:46:31,930
What are you doing here?

644
00:46:32,380 --> 00:46:34,370
Min told me to receive a brief
from a new client.

645
00:46:34,420 --> 00:46:35,540
She said it’s urgent.

646
00:46:36,180 --> 00:46:37,370
All her works are urgent.

647
00:46:37,700 --> 00:46:40,780
She said the client is a clothing brand.

648
00:46:41,220 --> 00:46:42,580
Their brand is not widely known.

649
00:46:42,620 --> 00:46:44,380
So they want to make a fashion video.

650
00:46:44,850 --> 00:46:46,670
They have a high budget.
So I quickly accepted this job.

651
00:46:46,740 --> 00:46:48,020
We do it for money.

652
00:46:54,300 --> 00:46:54,900
Gorya.

653
00:46:55,900 --> 00:46:57,400
I’m sorry about that night.

654
00:46:59,370 --> 00:47:00,940
It’s okay. I understand.

655
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:05,690
Is she the one you can’t get over?

656
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:09,800
Yes.

657
00:47:10,260 --> 00:47:14,380
I’d been dating her since college
until I started to work.

658
00:47:14,690 --> 00:47:15,810
We were dating for several years.

659
00:47:16,130 --> 00:47:17,070
She suddenly came back.

660
00:47:17,110 --> 00:47:18,700
I don’t know what she wants.

661
00:47:25,060 --> 00:47:26,430
Whatever she wants from you.

662
00:47:27,300 --> 00:47:28,450
If you don’t give it to her,

663
00:47:29,560 --> 00:47:30,900
there’s nothing she can do.

664
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:34,500
Let’s go in.

665
00:47:37,420 --> 00:47:39,140
Do you have any information about them?

666
00:47:39,690 --> 00:47:40,780
Could they be a scammer?

667
00:47:41,140 --> 00:47:42,080
I don’t think so.

668
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:43,690
I heard that they are a new brand.

669
00:47:43,960 --> 00:47:45,250
I think they want to keep it a secret.

670
00:47:45,630 --> 00:47:46,850
They wanted to pick the staff themselves.

671
00:47:47,100 --> 00:47:48,470
They specifically requested you.

672
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:50,340
So I picked the team that you trust
to work on this project.

673
00:47:50,630 --> 00:47:51,850
Gorya will take care of the clothing.

674
00:47:52,260 --> 00:47:53,980
Praew will take
the behind-the-scenes photos.

675
00:47:54,220 --> 00:47:55,310
I want to give her a try.

676
00:47:58,350 --> 00:47:59,220
A try for what?

677
00:48:00,770 --> 00:48:02,050
I want to see how she works.

678
00:48:02,100 --> 00:48:02,940
What are you thinking?

679
00:48:03,220 --> 00:48:03,940
Is that so?

680
00:48:13,920 --> 00:48:15,210
Damn, are you serious?

681
00:48:16,360 --> 00:48:17,400
Hello, Shasha.

682
00:48:25,880 --> 00:48:28,300
Yes, the client wants her to be
the model for this collection.

683
00:48:28,570 --> 00:48:31,400
Be nice to her for money.

684
00:48:32,490 --> 00:48:33,700
This is a dream team.

685
00:48:36,710 --> 00:48:37,650
Hello, Gorya.

686
00:48:40,600 --> 00:48:41,720
I can’t seem to avoid you.

687
00:48:43,980 --> 00:48:45,400
When did they say the meeting would begin?

688
00:48:48,430 --> 00:48:49,260
1 p.m.

689
00:48:49,540 --> 00:48:50,370
1 p.m.?

690
00:48:50,570 --> 00:48:51,980
But it’s almost 2 p.m.

691
00:48:52,340 --> 00:48:53,150
I know they are our client.

692
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:55,450
But they should have told us
if they would be late.

693
00:48:55,700 --> 00:48:58,030
If I knew they would be this late,
I would have waited in my office.

694
00:48:58,070 --> 00:49:00,200
They should show us some respect.

695
00:49:11,250 --> 00:49:12,200
Your client is here.

696
00:49:12,810 --> 00:49:13,940
Shall we begin the meeting?

697
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:37,980
Cut.

698
00:49:38,760 --> 00:49:41,490
If you approach me
by pretending to be my client,

699
00:49:42,000 --> 00:49:43,100
I’m telling you it won’t work.

700
00:49:43,770 --> 00:49:46,600
Did you hire a Michelin-star chef
to cook at your condo?

701
00:49:46,740 --> 00:49:47,930
Only for a special date.

702
00:49:48,820 --> 00:49:49,730
Then what?

703
00:49:50,290 --> 00:49:52,600
Even though you look really pretty
when you cry,

704
00:49:52,960 --> 00:49:54,740
I still want to see you smile.
